      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/45/17",
      "text": [
        ":\nقُلْتُ لِأَبِي اَلْحَسَنِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ يَكُونُ لِلرَّجُلِ اَلْخَصِيُّ يَدْخُلُ عَلَى نِسَائِهِ يُنَاوِلُهُنَّ اَلْوَضُوءَ فَيَرَى شُعُورَهُنَّ قَالَ \"لاَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4633 - It is narrated from Muhammad ibn Ishaq ibn Ammar that he said: I asked Abu al-Hasan (as): \"Can a eunuch belonging to a man enter upon his women and hand them water for ablution, thereby seeing their hair?\"\nThe Imam (as) replied: \"No.\""
        ]
      }
